00:31:51.326 --> 00:31:52.493
[Danny laughing]

488
00:31:53.661 --> 00:31:55.538
[Danny]
Yeah. You got it.

489
00:31:56.623 --> 00:31:58.625
[♪♪♪]

490
00:31:59.709 --> 00:32:02.337
[John]
<i>I'm not saying I'm a hero for what I did.</i>

491
00:32:05.089 --> 00:32:07.508
<i>A man's supposed to
look out for his brother.</i>

492
00:32:11.804 --> 00:32:14.265
<i>That's what family's all about.</i>

493
00:32:19.062 --> 00:32:22.190
<i>In a way. it wasn't just him
I was trying to save.</i>

494
00:32:27.278 --> 00:32:29.781
<i>I was trying to save myself.</i>

495
00:32:30.782 --> 00:32:33.368
<i>I was trying to save all of us.</i>

496
00:32:41.334 --> 00:32:43.336
[indistinct radio chatter]

497
00:32:46.005 --> 00:32:47.924
Sorry to ruin the night.

498
00:33:16.244 --> 00:33:21.374
[Diana] John. honey? Is that you?
Come to bed.

499
00:33:43.563 --> 00:33:46.357
[Diana] <i>This girl you brought
to the party.</i>

500
00:33:46.441 --> 00:33:48.568
-[Danny] <i>Sheryl?</i>
-Is that something serious?

501
00:33:49.235 --> 00:33:51.404
I'm not sure. We'll see.

502
00:33:52.071 --> 00:33:54.949
I met a good one a couple of months ago.

503
00:33:55.158 --> 00:33:56.784
- Good lady.
- Yeah?

504
00:33:57.201 --> 00:34:01.330
We go out a few times.
It was fine. good. perfectly normal.

505
00:34:01.539 --> 00:34:03.332
- Good for you. Dan.
- Yeah.

506
00:34:03.541 --> 00:34:05.585
And then. you know...

507
00:34:06.502 --> 00:34:08.171
eventually...

508
00:34:09.505 --> 00:34:13.468
We. you know.
start going at it. you know.

509
00:34:14.844 --> 00:34:18.139
- Mm-hm.
- And. um. she says...

510
00:34:18.347 --> 00:34:20.058
"Hit me."

511
00:34:21.601 --> 00:34:23.144
Like "hit her" hit her.

512
00:34:23.352 --> 00:34:25.772
Wanted me to hit her in the face.

513
00:34:25.980 --> 00:34:28.066
What? Why?

514
00:34:28.274 --> 00:34:31.110
I don't know. I told her
I don't do that kind of thing.

515
00:34:32.737 --> 00:34:34.489
Well. good.

516
00:34:34.697 --> 00:34:36.032
Heh.

517
00:34:36.240 --> 00:34:40.203
I mean. truth is. I didn't really know
if I wanted to fuck her or not.

518
00:34:41.496 --> 00:34:44.707
She says again. "Hit me."

519
00:34:44.916 --> 00:34:48.211
And I said no again.

520
00:34:48.961 --> 00:34:53.216
Then she whacks me with her fist.

521
00:34:53.424 --> 00:34:56.010
And I thought she broke my nose.

522
00:35:03.142 --> 00:35:08.731
I realized that she was doing it so.
you know. I'd get mad and I'd hit her.

523
00:35:24.205 --> 00:35:27.750
- [John] Fred. how are you?
- [Fred] I'm good. John.

524
00:35:28.334 --> 00:35:30.920
- [John] How long you been out here?
- Not too long.

525
00:35:31.129 --> 00:35:33.631
How's this for timing?
Your big family weekend and all.

526
00:35:33.840 --> 00:35:35.967
Yeah. it's the way it usually works out.

527
00:35:36.175 --> 00:35:38.010
Out here fishing for some snook. man.

528
00:35:38.219 --> 00:35:40.138
Going up and down the channel.
I saw that.

529
00:35:40.304 --> 00:35:41.889
Figured I'd give you guys a call.

530
00:35:42.348 --> 00:35:44.517
Just around the bend there.

531
00:35:45.768 --> 00:35:47.478
So I hope you left.

532
00:35:48.855 --> 00:35:50.773
No.

533
00:35:51.232 --> 00:35:55.444
Because then she starts screaming.
kicking me.

534
00:35:55.653 --> 00:36:00.658
And I fall off the bed.
You know. the lamp topples over.

535
00:36:00.867 --> 00:36:02.702
Why didn't you just leave? Seems...

536
00:36:02.910 --> 00:36:07.081
How could I? She came after me. right?
She's still screaming. carrying on.

537
00:36:07.290 --> 00:36:09.208
I pin her down to the ground
and I tell her.

538
00:36:09.292 --> 00:36:11.836
"You better calm the fuck down.
I will just leave."

539
00:36:12.044 --> 00:36:14.714
- This is horrible.
- We'll pretend like nothing happened.

540
00:36:14.839 --> 00:36:16.090
Yeah. Yeah.

541
00:36:16.257 --> 00:36:17.592
What did she say?

542
00:36:17.800 --> 00:36:22.930
She tells me how no one loves her.
And how now I'm just gonna leave

543
00:36:23.139 --> 00:36:28.561
like everyone else leaves.
So now I feel bad for her.

544
00:36:30.188 --> 00:36:33.566
- [Diana] Oh. man. This woman needs help.
- Yeah.

545
00:36:33.774 --> 00:36:38.863
So I stayed the night with her.
I ended up seeing her for a few months.

546
00:36:45.912 --> 00:36:49.373
I don't think it was meant to be.
It's so hard to find the right one.

547
00:36:49.582 --> 00:36:51.626
I'm sure it's lonely.

548
00:36:53.836 --> 00:36:55.338
Yeah.

549
00:36:55.546 --> 00:36:57.048
I'd love to see John single.

550
00:36:57.215 --> 00:37:00.384
I'd love to watch him play the field.
See what it's like.

551
00:37:03.512 --> 00:37:06.265
Seriously. even just for a week.

552
00:37:07.475 --> 00:37:09.477
[♪♪♪]

553
00:37:17.151 --> 00:37:18.319
[John]
Hold it. Tommy.

554
00:37:20.446 --> 00:37:21.948
Marco.

555
00:37:30.998 --> 00:37:33.000
[insect buzzing]

556
00:37:42.885 --> 00:37:44.262
Marco.

557
00:37:49.267 --> 00:37:50.559
Shit.

558
00:37:51.185 --> 00:37:53.437
Tommy. keep it right there.

559
00:37:53.771 --> 00:37:55.314
[Tommy]
Okay.

560
00:38:09.036 --> 00:38:11.497
Jesus. John.
She can't be more than 16.

561
00:38:18.462 --> 00:38:22.925
Call in the ME. Get a team down here.

562
00:38:25.761 --> 00:38:28.389
Goddamn it. it's gonna be a long night.

563
00:38:38.024 --> 00:38:40.484
[Danny]
Now. listen. man. I gotta talk to you.

564
00:38:40.901 --> 00:38:46.866
This job. I... I appreciate it. the offer.
but I can't do it.

565
00:38:47.658 --> 00:38:49.827
What the fuck? Why?

566
00:38:50.244 --> 00:38:53.831
Looks like I'm gonna be
going to work with my parents.

567
00:38:53.998 --> 00:38:55.708
I don't wanna fuck it up.

568
00:38:56.709 --> 00:38:58.502
They asked you to come back?

569
00:38:59.253 --> 00:39:01.130
John's talking to the old man about it.

570
00:39:01.339 --> 00:39:04.425
Do you think he's gonna
welcome you back with open arms?

571
00:39:04.592 --> 00:39:06.177
"Danny. come home."

572
00:39:07.303 --> 00:39:09.138
John will take care of it.

573
00:39:09.347 --> 00:39:10.973
How do you know?

574
00:39:12.016 --> 00:39:14.935
'Cause that's what he does.
Takes care of shit.

575
00:39:30.493 --> 00:39:31.702
There we go.

576
00:39:32.370 --> 00:39:36.040
[Eric] Yum. yum. lunch.
Look at that beautiful bastard.

577
00:39:36.165 --> 00:39:37.458
- Ha-ha-ha.
- I can get more.

578
00:39:37.666 --> 00:39:39.210
Well. go. Cousteau.

579
00:39:39.418 --> 00:39:41.879
Can't sit over these traps all day.

580
00:39:42.421 --> 00:39:43.964
Dive.

581
00:39:51.555 --> 00:39:53.557
[♪♪♪]

582
00:40:07.446 --> 00:40:09.115
What do you got. man?

583
00:40:13.244 --> 00:40:14.912
What is that?

584
00:40:17.164 --> 00:40:19.291
Whoa. dude.

585
00:40:22.503 --> 00:40:23.879
You're bleeding. bro.

586
00:40:24.797 --> 00:40:25.840
Oh.

587
00:40:32.805 --> 00:40:34.807
[ukulele playing]

588
00:40:35.433 --> 00:40:37.726
[chattering]

589
00:40:39.395 --> 00:40:41.772
[Robert singing indistinctly]

590
00:40:46.861 --> 00:40:48.904
[people cheering]

591
00:40:51.031 --> 00:40:53.033
♪ <i>Do I have to be?</i> ♪

592
00:40:54.827 --> 00:40:56.912
♪ <i>Can I get you anything?</i> ♪

593
00:40:57.121 --> 00:40:59.498
[John] How come you're not
out there playing?

594
00:40:59.832 --> 00:41:01.292
[John grunts]

595
00:41:01.500 --> 00:41:07.131
Thanks. You know. sometimes it's
just nice to sit back and watch your kids.

596
00:41:07.506 --> 00:41:09.133
[John chuckles]

597
00:41:13.471 --> 00:41:15.431
What's on your mind. Johnny?

598
00:41:22.688 --> 00:41:24.482
Danny wants to come home.

599
00:41:24.982 --> 00:41:29.695
Heh. Home? What does that mean.
"come home?"

600
00:41:29.904 --> 00:41:32.198
He wants to help out with the business.

601
00:41:34.116 --> 00:41:36.911
What makes him think we need help?

602
00:41:37.119 --> 00:41:39.079
Just telling you what he said.

603
00:41:40.414 --> 00:41:42.082
Oh. I see.

604
00:41:42.208 --> 00:41:43.250
[screams]

605
00:41:43.334 --> 00:41:45.628
Mom! Help!

606
00:41:47.505 --> 00:41:51.258
I think he's serious this time. I think
this is something that he really wants.

607
00:41:52.551 --> 00:41:55.721
And you think
I should let him come home?

608
00:41:59.141 --> 00:42:01.769
My opinion is it makes Mom happier
when he's around.

609
00:42:01.977 --> 00:42:05.064
Oh. yeah. It makes Mom happier.
until he fucks up again.

610
00:42:08.651 --> 00:42:10.694
[woman]
Whoo! My hero!

611
00:42:10.778 --> 00:42:12.780
[♪♪♪]

612
00:42:17.034 --> 00:42:21.539
I think you three should
make the decision about Danny.

613
00:42:25.918 --> 00:42:29.964
You discuss it with Meg and Kevin.

614
00:42:30.714 --> 00:42:32.758
Whatever you decide.

615
00:42:32.925 --> 00:42:34.969
I'll live with it.

616
00:42:40.766 --> 00:42:46.397
♪ <i>You are my sunshine
My only sunshine</i> ♪

617
00:42:47.439 --> 00:42:50.234
♪ <i>You make me happy</i> ♪

618
00:42:51.110 --> 00:42:53.237
♪ <i>When skies are gray</i> ♪

619
00:42:54.947 --> 00:42:59.451
[Kevin] Look. if we say yes.
no good will come of this.

620
00:42:59.660 --> 00:43:01.287
You guys know it.

621
00:43:01.495 --> 00:43:05.666
Things will be nice for a little while.
he'll be on his best behavior.

622
00:43:05.833 --> 00:43:07.668
you know. just long enough

623
00:43:07.876 --> 00:43:11.171
for Mom to get sucked back
into his bullshit.

624
00:43:11.380 --> 00:43:14.508
Then he'll fuck it up.
and then she'll get crushed.

625
00:43:15.175 --> 00:43:17.928
Don't be an asshole. You know what?
People can change.

626
00:43:18.137 --> 00:43:19.680
People can change. he can't.

627
00:43:21.682 --> 00:43:24.101
I just don't see
how we can say no to him.

628
00:43:24.852 --> 00:43:28.731
What do you wanna do? Treat him
like an outcast for the rest of his life?

629
00:43:28.939 --> 00:43:32.693
No. it's not personal. you know.
I like Danny. I like him. We can hang out.

630
00:43:32.901 --> 00:43:35.154
We can have a laugh. but...

631
00:43:35.988 --> 00:43:39.241
Danny helping
to run the family business?

632
00:43:39.450 --> 00:43:41.785
We have to think about
Mom and Dad here.

633
00:43:41.994 --> 00:43:44.622
Well. the thing is that Dad
left the decision with us. guys.

634
00:43:44.705 --> 00:43:45.623
[Meg sighs]

635
00:43:45.706 --> 00:43:48.459
I don't know why he did that.
Why do we have to decide?

636
00:43:48.667 --> 00:43:51.587
He will fuck things up.

637
00:43:52.671 --> 00:43:53.922
You know he will.

638
00:43:54.131 --> 00:43:56.383
And fucking old Ruth
comes back home.

639
00:43:56.592 --> 00:43:58.927
-[chattering indistinctly]
-[rock music playing over speakers]

640
00:43:59.011 --> 00:44:01.305
[Eric]
Yeah. baby.

641
00:44:02.181 --> 00:44:04.850
[all laughing and whooping]

642
00:44:05.893 --> 00:44:07.478
[grunts and sniffs]

643
00:44:07.811 --> 00:44:11.106
So John's gonna talk to your old man?

644
00:44:11.315 --> 00:44:14.401
You need permission
to go work for your family.

645
00:44:14.610 --> 00:44:16.654
That place is your fucking
birthright. man.

646
00:44:16.862 --> 00:44:18.405
Yeah. Well...

647
00:44:18.572 --> 00:44:23.661
Don't fucking go begging.
you know. those fucking assholes.

648
00:44:23.869 --> 00:44:26.205
- Yeah. Okay.
- Okay?

649
00:44:27.081 --> 00:44:29.708
Come work for me. man.
What do you say?

650
00:44:29.917 --> 00:44:33.045
You stick around.
you make some big time scratch.

651
00:44:33.253 --> 00:44:36.799
You won't need
a goddamn thing from the Rayburns.

652
00:44:37.758 --> 00:44:41.011
Danny. I'm just saying
that your family...

653
00:44:41.762 --> 00:44:44.556
they don't give
a fucking shit about you. man.

654
00:44:45.099 --> 00:44:46.266
They don't give a shit...

655
00:44:46.475 --> 00:44:49.103
Even when we were kids
they didn't give a shit about you.

656
00:44:49.311 --> 00:44:51.480
They treat you like
you're some fucking plague.

657
00:44:51.647 --> 00:44:53.273
- They do.
- Stop it. stop it.

658
00:44:53.482 --> 00:44:55.984
Like they can't wait to get rid of you
or something.

659
00:44:56.193 --> 00:45:00.781
I'm telling you as your friend.
as your buddy. okay. your family...

660
00:45:00.989 --> 00:45:03.242
they're the enemy. man.

661
00:45:13.627 --> 00:45:15.295
I think we have to
give him a chance.

662
00:45:15.504 --> 00:45:18.507
It's asinine that
we're even considering this.

663
00:45:24.388 --> 00:45:26.557
If we say no to him.

664
00:45:27.307 --> 00:45:31.311
he will leave.
And I'm not so sure he'll come back.

665
00:45:32.646 --> 00:45:34.273
Why? What makes you think that?

666
00:45:38.402 --> 00:45:40.112
It's just a feeling I have.

667
00:45:41.780 --> 00:45:43.323
You gotta fucking move on.

668
00:45:43.532 --> 00:45:46.410
- Enough. all right?
- You gotta say. "Fuck my family."

669
00:45:46.618 --> 00:45:49.746
Come on. You gotta get over it already.

670
00:45:49.955 --> 00:45:53.167
Fuck your family.
Fuck the goddamn family business.

671
00:45:53.667 --> 00:45:57.504
Fuck the fucking Rayburns.
They hate you. man. They always will.

672
00:45:57.713 --> 00:45:59.756
Jesus fucking Christ.

673
00:45:59.965 --> 00:46:05.095
Hey. man. Whoa. I'm just trying to help.
I'm on your side.

674
00:46:05.304 --> 00:46:07.222
[Kevin]
<i>So we say yes.</i>

675
00:46:07.431 --> 00:46:10.767
And he comes back. You know who's
gonna get the worst of it. don't you?

676
00:46:10.976 --> 00:46:12.269
You.

677
00:46:12.352 --> 00:46:13.562
[Meg grunts]

678
00:46:13.645 --> 00:46:17.983
John. as soon as things turn to shit.
he's gonna come straight back to you.

679
00:46:18.192 --> 00:46:20.944
There's a lot of shit Danny
did for me when we were kids

680
00:46:21.111 --> 00:46:22.905
that you don't know anything about.

681
00:46:28.702 --> 00:46:30.871
I want Danny in my life.

682
00:46:32.080 --> 00:46:34.166
I want him to know my children.

683
00:46:38.295 --> 00:46:40.672
Goddamn it.
you don't give up on family.

684
00:46:42.341 --> 00:46:44.218
Do you want him to stay?

685
00:46:50.724 --> 00:46:52.059
Yeah.

686
00:46:56.772 --> 00:46:59.608
[woman] I was surprised
to see you get off that bus.

687
00:47:03.195 --> 00:47:05.405
You should take it easy
with those things.

688
00:47:05.531 --> 00:47:07.032
Why don't you try one?

689
00:47:07.157 --> 00:47:12.287
No. I don't need any.
I'm not in any pain.

690
00:47:19.127 --> 00:47:21.129
You gonna stay after the weekend?

691
00:47:21.338 --> 00:47:22.965
Maybe I should go with you.

692
00:47:24.716 --> 00:47:26.426
I don't think that's a good idea.

693
00:47:26.635 --> 00:47:30.514
Stay or go.
It's not even up to me anymore.

694
00:47:34.351 --> 00:47:36.061
Fuck it.

695
00:47:44.987 --> 00:47:46.029
[chuckles]

696
00:47:47.281 --> 00:47:49.658
Know what I wanna do right now?

697
00:47:51.827 --> 00:47:53.829
-[Danny laughing]
-[woman shouts]

698
00:48:05.799 --> 00:48:07.884
[woman]
What's the matter?

699
00:48:08.093 --> 00:48:10.887
- Can't keep up?
- Oh!

700
00:48:10.971 --> 00:48:13.265
[♪♪♪]

701
00:48:14.683 --> 00:48:17.686
Hey. Wait!

702
00:48:21.648 --> 00:48:23.358
[grunting and groaning]

703
00:48:37.122 --> 00:48:41.251
[muffled shouting]

704
00:48:59.019 --> 00:49:00.395
[coughing]

705
00:49:01.480 --> 00:49:03.482
[Danny gasping]

706
00:49:04.024 --> 00:49:06.026
[♪♪♪]

707
00:49:19.289 --> 00:49:21.458
[man]
Is that Danny out there?

708
00:49:23.960 --> 00:49:25.962
[chattering]

709
00:49:26.046 --> 00:49:27.631
[♪♪♪]

710
00:49:55.200 --> 00:49:58.412
Cover yourself. We have guests.

711
00:50:05.252 --> 00:50:07.003
[Danny groaning]

712
00:50:10.924 --> 00:50:12.300
[groans deeply]

713
00:50:24.730 --> 00:50:27.190
[Danny]
Oh. shit...

714
00:50:30.527 --> 00:50:32.654
[Danny coughing]

715
00:50:44.624 --> 00:50:48.837
[Danny] I can't remember
the first time that I caught a fish.

716
00:50:52.215 --> 00:50:53.300
Can you?

717
00:50:54.384 --> 00:50:56.636
[John]
You must have been with Dad.

718
00:50:58.722 --> 00:51:00.390
[Danny]
You remember yours?

719
00:51:01.224 --> 00:51:02.642
[John]
No.

720
00:51:02.851 --> 00:51:06.354
Oh. man. I do. Heh.

721
00:51:07.314 --> 00:51:12.819
You hooked a tarpon. Fucking hooked
a tarpon. Thing was twice your size.

722
00:51:13.028 --> 00:51:18.992
But Dad... he wasn't gonna help you.
He wanted you to reel it in yourself.

723
00:51:19.201 --> 00:51:21.119
I don't remember.

724
00:51:21.828 --> 00:51:24.915
Okay. Oh. man.

725
00:51:26.333 --> 00:51:29.628
Oh. I fucked up last night.

726
00:51:31.046 --> 00:51:32.798
I can't even remember what happened.

727
00:51:35.967 --> 00:51:38.303
I know it's not. um...

728
00:51:40.722 --> 00:51:44.810
easy having me here.
And I'm sure you. you know...

729
00:51:45.560 --> 00:51:48.438
- don't want me here.
- That's not true.

730
00:51:51.399 --> 00:51:53.777
That money I owe you.
I'm gonna pay it all back.

731
00:51:53.985 --> 00:51:56.905
I been keeping track of it.
I'm paying it back with interest.

732
00:52:05.080 --> 00:52:06.957
Dad gave me his answer.

733
00:52:09.543 --> 00:52:10.836
Oh...

734
00:52:11.795 --> 00:52:13.839
I'm sorry. man. It's not gonna work out.

735
00:52:13.922 --> 00:52:15.674
[Danny sighs]

736
00:52:17.342 --> 00:52:20.262
That's what he said?
He don't want me back?

737
00:52:20.470 --> 00:52:23.557
No. he didn't put it that way. He just...

738
00:52:26.101 --> 00:52:27.602
And what did you say?

739
00:52:27.811 --> 00:52:30.939
He's just not ready for it.
It's not a good time.

740
00:52:31.147 --> 00:52:34.192
No. is that what he thinks?
Or what you think?

741
00:52:36.862 --> 00:52:41.700
Don't do that. You asked me
to talk to him and I talked to him.

742
00:52:41.908 --> 00:52:43.869
Did you try to convince him?

743
00:52:45.412 --> 00:52:49.040
What do you want. huh?
What the fuck do you want?

744
00:52:49.207 --> 00:52:51.668
Do you need another loan?
You need somewhere to stay?

745
00:52:51.877 --> 00:52:53.253
Fuck you.

746
00:52:53.837 --> 00:52:55.630
How can I help you?

747
00:52:55.839 --> 00:52:58.008
Oh. yeah. You wanna help me.

748
00:52:58.216 --> 00:53:01.720
Like what? Like the way
you tried to convince Dad?

749
00:53:01.887 --> 00:53:06.600
Did everything in your power to get him
to change his fucking narrow mind

750
00:53:06.808 --> 00:53:09.060
and take me back?

751
00:53:12.022 --> 00:53:15.650
Or did you just sit there like
a good boy with your mouth shut?

752
00:53:16.860 --> 00:53:18.278
Like you always fucking do.

753
00:53:19.070 --> 00:53:21.865
I did what you asked me to do.

754
00:53:23.617 --> 00:53:28.288
Your life's not always gonna be
this perfect. Things happen to people.

755
00:53:32.709 --> 00:53:35.128
And then you'll need me.

756
00:53:36.046 --> 00:53:38.048
And then you'll know.

757
00:53:39.674 --> 00:53:42.177
What the fuck
am I gonna know. Danny?

758
00:53:42.385 --> 00:53:43.678
Huh?

759
00:53:43.887 --> 00:53:46.431
What the fuck
are you even talking about?

760
00:53:47.182 --> 00:53:48.934
Are you saying that I don't help you?

761
00:53:49.142 --> 00:53:52.312
Are you saying that my
whole life I haven't tried to help you?

762
00:53:52.896 --> 00:53:55.023
My whole fucking life.
that's what I've done.

763
00:53:55.231 --> 00:53:59.778
I've fucking tried to protect you.
I've tried to protect big brother.

764
00:54:05.700 --> 00:54:07.452
I'll leave tonight.

765
00:54:09.704 --> 00:54:11.122
Don't do that.

766
00:54:11.498 --> 00:54:15.710
The bonfire's tonight.
The pier dedication's in the morning.

767
00:54:28.598 --> 00:54:32.018
The secret of life?
Knowing when to leave.

768
00:54:32.102 --> 00:54:33.645
[♪♪♪]

769
00:54:35.271 --> 00:54:37.273
[chattering in distance]

770
00:54:54.207 --> 00:54:55.458
[all laughing]

771
00:54:57.794 --> 00:54:59.504
What?

772
00:54:59.587 --> 00:55:02.465
[people chattering indistinctly]

773
00:55:04.509 --> 00:55:06.511
[♪♪♪]

774
00:55:42.964 --> 00:55:45.592
[chattering indistinctly]

775
00:56:01.608 --> 00:56:04.486
[John] You sure you don't wanna
stick around for the ceremony?

776
00:56:08.782 --> 00:56:10.992
Are you asking me to stay?

777
00:56:20.168 --> 00:56:21.961
Don't worry about it.

778
00:56:28.051 --> 00:56:29.719
Hey. Danny.

779
00:56:33.223 --> 00:56:35.767
Maybe I'll see you at Christmas. huh?

780
00:56:38.144 --> 00:56:40.146
[♪♪♪]

781
00:56:56.162 --> 00:56:58.957
[John] <i>I always thought the greatest thing
that happened to me</i>

782
00:56:59.165 --> 00:57:01.167
<i>was being born a Rayburn.</i>

783
00:57:08.341 --> 00:57:10.718
<i>Now I'm not so sure.</i>

784
00:57:21.479 --> 00:57:24.107
<i>I'm gonna tell you everything.</i>

785
00:57:26.734 --> 00:57:28.820
<i>It's not very pleasant.</i>

786
00:57:30.613 --> 00:57:32.657
<i>But it's the truth.</i>

787
00:57:36.244 --> 00:57:38.496
<i>What we did to our brother...</i>

788
00:57:39.122 --> 00:57:40.999
<i>we had to do.</i>

789
00:57:42.417 --> 00:57:44.919
<i>Please don't judge us.</i>

790
00:57:54.304 --> 00:57:56.431
<i>We're not bad people.</i>

791
00:57:58.308 --> 00:58:00.477
<i>But we did a bad thing.</i>

792
00:58:03.521 --> 00:58:05.482
[gasping]

793
00:58:21.915 --> 00:58:23.791
[♪♪♪]

794
00:58:23.875 --> 00:58:26.085
<i>♪ Will I live tomorrow? ♪</i>

795
00:58:27.629 --> 00:58:30.048
<i>♪ Well. I just can't say ♪</i>

796
00:58:31.674 --> 00:58:34.969
<i>♪ No. no sun coming through my windows ♪</i>

797
00:58:36.095 --> 00:58:39.265
<i>♪ Feels like I'm living
At the bottom of a grave ♪</i>

798
00:58:40.517 --> 00:58:43.645
<i>♪ I wish you'd hurry up and rescue me ♪</i>

799
00:58:44.812 --> 00:58:48.024
<i>♪ So I can be on my miserable way ♪</i>

800
00:58:48.983 --> 00:58:52.529
<i>♪ I don't live today ♪</i>

801
00:58:53.112 --> 00:58:56.783
<i>♪ Maybe tomorrow
I just can't say ♪</i>

801
